revision.text:
The eleventh season of [[Cuba]]'s primary amateur [[baseball]] league ended with a repeat champion. For the second straight year, Azucareros won the [[Cuban National Series]], defeating Mineros 2-1 games in best-of-three-playoffs after the teams tied for the best record in the league.
==Standings== {|class="wikitable" ! Team !! W !! L !! Pct. !! [[Games behind|GB]] |- | Azucareros || 52 || 14 || .787 || - |- | Mineros || 52 || 14 || .787 || - |- | [[Industriales]] || 51 || 15 || .772 || 1 |- | Granjeros || 49 || 17 || .742 || 3 |- | [[Henequeneros]] || 40 || 26 || .606 || 12 |- | [[La Habana (baseball team)|La Habana]] || 32 || 34 || .484 || 20 |- | [[Vegueros]] || 29 || 37 || .439 || 23 |- | Oriente || 24 || 42 || .363 || 28 |- | [[Camagüey (baseball team)|Camagüey]] || 19 || 47 || .287 || 33 |- | Las Villas || 18 || 48 || .272 || 34 |- | [[Pinar del Río (baseball team)|Pinar del Río]] || 17 || 49 || .257 || 35 |- | [[Matanzas (baseball team)|Matanzas]] || 13 || 53 || .190 || 39 |}
==Playoff for the championship (best-of-three)== Azucareros - Mineros 2 - 1 games
==Trivia== Mineros put together a 25-game winning streak during the season, while Matanzas lost 25 in a row.
