'''[[Cuba]]''' competed at the '''[[1900 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Paris]], [[France]].<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/CUB/summer/1900/ |title=Cuba:1900 Olympic Results |accessdate=2010-03-31 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>
==Medalists== {| class="wikitable sortable" style="font-size:90%" |- !Medal !Name !Sport !Event |- | {{Gold medal}} || {{sortname|Ramón|Fonst}} || [[Fencing at the 1900 Summer Olympics|Fencing]] || [[Fencing at the 1900 Summer Olympics – Men's épée|Men's épée]] |- | {{silver medal}} || {{sortname|Ramón|Fonst}} || [[Fencing at the 1900 Summer Olympics|Fencing]] || [[Fencing at the 1900 Summer Olympics – Men's amateurs-masters épée|Men's amateurs-masters épée]] |}
== Fencing== {{Main|Fencing at the 1900 Summer Olympics}}
Cuba had one fencer compete in the nation's debut. He won the amateur épée competition, and in a special event that pitted the top four amateurs in 1900 against the top four professionals, he defeated all but one of his opponents, finishing 6-1 to take the silver medal.
