'''''Excuse My Glove''''' is a 1936 British, [[black-and-white]] [[comedy film|comedy]] [[List of sports films|sports film]] [[film director|directed]] by [[Redd Davis]] starring [[Len Harvey]], and [[Bobbie Comber]].<ref>http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/32635?view=cast</ref> It was [[film producer|produced]] by Alexander Film Productions.

==Synopsis==
A young stained glass-worker accepts accidentally a challenge to fight in a boxing booth at a fair.

