{{DISPLAYTITLE: Judo Australia}} {{Infobox sport governing body |name = Judo Australia |abbrev = JA |logosize = |sport = [[Judo]] |image = File:Judo Australia logo.png |caption = Logo of Judo Australia |jurisdiction = [[Australia]] |founded = {{Start date|1952}} |aff = [[International Judo Federation|IJF]] |affdate = |region = [[Oceania Judo Union|OJU]] |regionyear = |headquarters = Australian Institute of Sport, Australian Capital Territory |location = |president = |chairperson = Kate Corkery |chiefexec = Alex Vallentine |vicepresident = |director = |secretary = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = www.ausjudo.com.au |countryflag = Australia }}
'''Judo Australia (JA)''' is the National Sporting Organisation recognised by the Australian Sports Commission for the [[sport]] of [[Judo]] in [[Australia]].
==History== The body was founded in [[Sydney]] in 1952.<ref>{{cite web|title=History of Judo in Australia|url=http://www.ausjudo.com.au/customdata/index.cfm?fuseaction=CustomItem&ItemID=49378|publisher=Judo Federation of Australia|accessdate=3 March 2013}}</ref>
==Structure== The national body has eight state member associations: * [http://www.judonsw.com.au/ Judo NSW]<ref>http://www.judonsw.com.au/</ref> * [https://judovictoria.com.au/ Judo Victoria]<ref>https://judovictoria.com.au/</ref> * [http://www.jfaq.com.au/ Judo Queensland]<ref>http://www.jfaq.com.au/</ref> * [https://www.judosa.com.au/ Judo SA]<ref>http://www.judosa.com.au/</ref> * [https://www.judowa.org.au/ Judo WA]<ref>http://www.judowa.org.au/</ref> * [http://www.judotasmania.org.au/ Judo Tasmania]<ref>http://www.judotasmania.org.au/</ref> * [http://www.judont.com.au/ Judo NT]<ref>http://www.judont.com.au/</ref> * [http://www.judoact.org/ Judo ACT]<ref>http://www.judoact.org/</ref>
The main tournament they organise is the annual [[Australian National Judo Championships]].
