'''Kashif Jawwad''' (born February 7, 1981, in [[Karachi]]) was a [[field hockey]] player and Former Hockey captain of [[Pakistan men's national field hockey team|Pakistan National Hockey Team]], he was part of the [[Pakistan men's national field hockey team|Pakistan National Hockey Team]] in two Olympic Games. He played 107 matches from [[Pakistan]] and he scored 51 goals in his career.

