{{Infobox sports league | logo=Nicaraguan Professional Baseball League Logo.png | pixels= | founded=1956 | sport=[[Baseball]] | country= [[Nicaragua]] | teams=4 | champion=Tigres del Chinandega | website=http://lbpn.com.ni/ {{Es icon}} }}
'''La Liga Nicaragüense de Beisbol Profesional (LNBP)''' was inaugurated on March 30, 1956, in Estadio Nacional. The first game was between the teams from San Fernando and Bóer. The [[Nicaragua]]n public's excitement for baseball grew as foreign [[professional baseball|professional]] teams and foreign players came to play in their country. Due to economic difficulty, the [[sports league|league]] had to shut down in 1967. The teams from Bóer and León were the most successful teams in those years with three championships each. The professional league was re-established in 2004.
