'''İbrahim Çolak''' (born {{birth date|1995|1|7|df=yes}}) is a Turkish male [[artistic gymnast]], representing his nation at international competitions. He won the bronze medal in the rings event at the [[2015 European Games]] in Baku. He competed at world championships, including the [[2014 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships]] in Nanning, China.<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 World Gymnastics Championships athletes - Ibrahim Colak|url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/00000D00020000FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF00|work=longinestiming.com|date= |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref>

